Identifies the cue point in seconds offset. Cue points are time instances where an ad can be inserted in the video. Value you either be SMPTE timecode offset or normal play time offset. Ref: https://www.ietf.org/rfc/rfc2326.txt Section3.5 and 3.6
Identifies a segment inerval of a media item

Start of the segment interval. Value can either be SMPTE timecode offset or normal play time offset. Ref: https://www.ietf.org/rfc/rfc2326.txt Section3.5 and 3.6. Also refer http://www.ebu.ch/metadata/ontologies/ebucore/ebucore#start

Start of the segment interval. Value can either be SMPTE timecode offset or normal play time offset. Ref: https://www.ietf.org/rfc/rfc2326.txt Section3.5 and 3.6. Also refer http://www.ebu.ch/metadata/ontologies/ebucore/ebucore#start

End of the segment interval. Value can either be SMPTE timecode offset or normal play time offset. Ref: https://www.ietf.org/rfc/rfc2326.txt Section3.5 and 3.6. Also refer http://www.ebu.ch/metadata/ontologies/ebucore/ebucore#end
Highly relevant keywords describing the media object. Max 10 elements. amg:keyword is unlooped representation of media:keywords. Ref: https://www.rssboard.org/media-rss#media-keywords
Episode number of an episodic item in the season is season is present otherwise episode number in the series
Long description describing media object
exampleValues: "movie on stock. Set in time persion 1929-1935"
